\par Prayer I, of St. Macarius the Great. 
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f39\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O Eternal God and King of all creation, Who hast vouchsafed me to arrive at this hour, forgive me the sins that I have committed this day in d
eed, word, and thought; and cleanse, O Lord, my lowly soul of all impurity of flesh and spirit, and grant me, O Lord, to pass the sleep of this night in peace; that, rising from my lowly bed, I may please Thy most holy name all the days of my life, and th
w
art the enemies, fleshly and bodiless, that war against me. And deliver me, O Lord, from vain thoughts and evil desires which defile me. For Thine is the kingdom, and the power, and the glory: of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now, an
d ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s61\ql \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f39\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayer II, of St. Antiochus:
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f39\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O Ruler of all, Word of the Father, O Jesus Christ, Thou Who art perfect: for the sake of the plenitude of Thy mercy, never depart from me, but always remain in me, Thy servant. O Jesus
, Good Shepherd of Thy sheep, deliver me not over to the sedition of the serpent, and leave me not to the will of Satan, for the seed of corruption is in me. But do Thou, O Lord, worshipful God, Holy King, Jesus Christ, as I sleep, guard me by the Unwanin
g
 Light, Thy Holy Spirit, by Whom Thou didst sanctify Thy disciples. O Lord, grant me, thine unworthy servant, Thy salvation upon my bed. Enlighten my mind with the light of understanding of Thy Holy Gospel; my soul, with the love of Thy Cross; my heart, w
i
th the purity of Thy word; my body, with Thy passionless passion. Keep my thoughts in Thy humility, and raise me up at the proper time for Thy glorification. For most glorified art Thou together with Thine unoriginate Father, and the Most Holy Spirit, unt
o the ages. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s61\ql \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f39\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayer III, to the Most Holy Spirit:
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f39\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O Lord, H
eavenly King, Comforter, Spirit of Truth, show compassion and have mercy on me, Thy sinful servant, and loose me from mine unworthiness, and forgive all wherein I have sinned against Thee today as a man, and not only as a man, but even worse than a beast,
 
my sins voluntary and involuntary, known and unknown, whether from youth, and from evil suggestion, or whether from brazenness and despondency. If I have sworn by Thy name, or blasphemed it in my thoughts; or grieved anyone, or have become angry about any
t
hing; or have lied, or slept needlessly, or if a beggar hath come to me and I disdained him; or if I have grieved my brother, or have quarreled, or have condemned anyone; or if I have been boastful, or prideful, or angry; if, as I stood at prayer, my mind
 
hath been distracted by the wiles of this world, or by thoughts of depravity; if I have overeaten, or have drunk excessively, or laughed frivolously; if I have thought evil, or have seen the beauty of another and been wounded thereby in my heart; if I hav
e
 said improper things, or derided my brother's sin when mine own sins are countless; if I have been neglectful of prayer, or have done some other wrong that I cannot remember, for all of this and more than this have I done: have mercy, O Master my Creator
,
 on me Thy downcast and unworthy servant, and loose me, and remit, and forgive me, for Thou art good and the Lover of mankind, so that, lustful, sinful, and wretched as I am, I may lie down and sleep and rest in peace. And I shall worship, and hymn, and g
lorify Thy most honorable name, together with the Father and His Only-begotten Son, now and ever, and unto the ages. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s61\ql \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\tx2520\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f39\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayer IV, of St. Macarius the Great
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f39\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par What shall I offer Thee, or what shall I give Thee, O greatly-gifted, immortal King, O compassi
onate Lord Who lovest mankind? For though I have been slothful in pleasing Thee, and have done nothing good, Thou hast led me to the close of this day that is past, establishing the conversion and salvation of my soul. Be merciful to me a sinner, bereft o
f
 every good deed, raise up my fallen soul which hath become defiled by countless sins, and take away from me every evil thought of this visible life. Forgive my sins, O Only Sinless One, in which I have sinned against Thee this day, known or unknown, in w
o
rd, and deed, and thought and in all my senses. Do Thou Thyself protect and guard me from every opposing circumstance, by Thy Divine authority and power and inexpressible love for mankind. Blot out, O God, blot out the multitude of my sins. Be pleased, O 
L
ord, to deliver me from the net of the Evil One, and save my passionate soul, and overshadow me with the light of Thy countenance when Thou shalt come in glory; and cause me, uncondemned now, to sleep a dreamless sleep, and keep Thy servant untroubled by 
t
houghts, and drive away from me all satanic deeds; and enlighten for me the eyes of my heart with understanding, lest I sleep unto death. And send me an angel of peace, a guardian and guide of my soul and body, that he may deliver me from mine enemies; th
a
t, rising from my bed, I may offer Thee prayers of thanksgiving. Yea, O Lord, hearken unto me, Thy sinful and wretched servant, in confession and conscience; grant me, when I arise, to be instructed by Thy sayings; and through Thine angels cause demonic d
e
spondency to be driven far from me: that I may bless Thy holy name, and glorify and extol the most pure Theotokos Mary, whom Thou hast given to us sinners as a protectress, and accept her who prayeth for us. For I know that she exemplifieth Thy love for m
ankind and prayeth for us without ceasing. Through her protection, and the sign of the precious Cross, and for the sake of all Thy saints, preserve my wretched soul, O Jesus Christ our God: for holy art Thou, and most glorious for ever. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s61\ql \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f39\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayer V
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f39\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O L
ord our God, as Thou art good and the Lover of mankind, forgive me wherein I have sinned today in word, deed, and thought. Grant me peaceful and undisturbed sleep; send Thy guardian angel to protect and keep me from evil. For Thou art the Guardian of our 
souls and bodies, and unto Thee do we send up glory: to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayer VI
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f39\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O Lord our God, in Whom we believe and Whose Name we invoke above every name, grant us
, as we go to sleep, relaxation of soul and body, and keep us from all dreams, and dark pleasures; stop the onslaught of the passions and quench the burnings that arise in the flesh. Grant us to live chastely in deed and word, that we may obtain a virtuou
s life, and not fall away from Thy promised blessings; for blessed art Thou for ever. Amen.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 
Prayer VII, of St. John Chrysostom, according to the number of hours of day and night: 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\ql \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f39\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f39\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 O Lord, deprive me not of Thy heavenly good things. 
\par O Lord, deliver me from the eternal torments. 
\par O Lord, if I have sinned in mind or thought, in word or deed, forgive me. 
\par O Lord, deliver me from all ignorance, forgetfulness, faint-heartedness, and stony insensibility. 
\par O Lord, deliver me from every temptation. 
\par O Lord, enlighten my heart which evil desire hath darkened. 
\par O Lord, as a man I have sinned, but do Thou, as the compassionate God, have mercy on me, seeing the infirmity of my soul. 
\par O Lord, send Thy grace to my help, that I may glorify Thy holy name. 
\par O Lord Jesus Christ, write me Thy servant in the Book of Life, and grant me a good end. 
\par O Lord my God, even though I have done nothing good in Thy sight, yet grant me by Thy grace to make a good beginning. 
\par O Lord, sprinkle into my heart the dew of Thy grace. 
\par O Lord of heaven and earth, remember me Thy sinful servant, shameful and unclean, in Thy kingdom. Amen.
\par 
\par O Lord, accept me in penitence. 
\par O Lord, forsake me not. O Lord, lead me not into temptation. 
\par O Lord, grant me good thoughts. 
\par O Lord, grant me tears, and remembrance of death, and compunction. 
\par O Lord, grant me the thought of confessing my sins. 
\par O Lord, grant me humility, chastity, and obedience. 
\par O Lord, grant me patience, courage, and meekness. 
\par O Lord, implant in me the root of good, Thy fear in my heart. 
\par O Lord, vouchsafe me to love Thee with all my soul and thoughts, and in all things to do Thy will. 
\par O Lord, protect me from evil men, and demons, and passions, and from every other unseemly thing. 
\par O Lord, Thou knowest that Thou doest as Thou wilt: Thy will be done also in me a sinner; for blessed art Thou unto the ages. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 Prayer VIII, to our Lord Jesus Christ
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f39\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O Lord Jesus Christ, Son of God, for the sake of Thy most honorable Mother, and Thy bodiless angels, Thy Prophet and Forerunner and Ba
ptist, the God-inspired apostles, the radiant and victorious martyrs, the holy and God-bearing fathers, and through the intercessions of all the saints, deliver me from the besetting presence of the demons. Yea, my Lord and Creator, Who desirest not the d
e
ath of the sinner, but rather that he be converted and live, grant conversion also to me, wretched and unworthy; rescue me from the mouth of the pernicious serpent, who is yawning to devour me and take me down to Hades alive. Yea, my Lord, my Comfort, Who
 
for my miserable sake wast clothed in corruptible flesh, draw me out of misery, and grant comfort to my miserable soul. Implant in my heart to fulfill Thy commandments, and to forsake evil deeds, and to obtain Thy blessings; for in Thee, O Lord, have I ho
ped, save me.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\insrsid7473308\charrsid394076 
\par }{\cs55\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\insrsid394076 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid8747982 
Prayer IX, to the Most Holy Theotokos
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f39\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par O good Mother of the Good King, most pure and blessed Theotokos Mary, do thou pour out the mercy of thy Son and our God upon my passionate soul, and by thine intercessions guide me unto 
good works, that I may pass the remaining time of my life without blemish, and attain paradise through thee, O Virgin Theotokos, who alone art pure and blessed.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid394076 Prayer X, to the Holy Guardian Angel}{\cs55\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\ql \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f39\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f39\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 O Angel of Christ, my holy guardian and protector of my 
soul and body, forgive me all wherein I have sinned this day, and deliver me from all opposing evil of mine enemy, lest I anger my God by any sin. Pray for me, a sinful and unworthy servant, that thou mayest show me forth worthy of the kindness and mercy 
of the All-holy Trinity, and of the Mother of my Lord Jesus Christ, and of all the saints. Amen.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6953665 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 Then, the Kontakion of the Theotokos:
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f39\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par To Thee the Champion Leader, we thy servants dedicate a feast of victory and of thanksgiving, as ones rescued out of sufferings, O Theotokos; but as thou art one with might which is invincible, from all dangers that can be, do thou deliver us, that we may
 cry to thee: Rejoice, thou Bride unwedded!
\par 
\par Most glorious Ever-Virgin, Mother of Christ God, present our prayer to thy Son and our God, that through thee our souls may be saved
\par 
\par All my hope I place in thee, O Mother of God: keep me under thy protection.
\par 
\par O Virgin Theotokos, disdain not me a sinner, needing thy help and thy protection, and have mercy on me, for my soul hath hoped in thee.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6953665 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 Then the prayer of St. Joannicius: 
\par }\pard\plain \s60\qj \li0\ri0\sl240\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f39\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning24\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\f1\fs32\insrsid7473308 My hope is the Father, my refuge is the Son, my protection is the Holy Spirit: O Ho
ly Trinity, glory to Thee.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 The end of the prayers approaching sleep. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid13046292 
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13046292 {\f1\fs32\insrsid13046292 ----------
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid13046292 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Here, the Order of Great Compline is resumed: 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  Glory to Thee, O God, our hope, glory to Thee. 
\par }{\cs59\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid7473308 Choir:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. Lord, have mercy.}{
\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (Thrice)}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6953665  }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Father, bless.}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 The priest saith aloud, while we prostrate ourselves to the earth (except on Fridays, when the lesser dismissal is used:) 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  O Master plenteous in mercy, O L
ord Jesus Christ our God: Through the intercessions of our immaculate Lady Theotokos and Ever-virgin Mary; through the power of the precious and life-giving Cross; through the mediations of the honorable, heavenly Bodiless Hosts, of the honorable, gloriou
s Prophet, Forerunner, and Baptist John; of the holy glorious, and all-praised apostles; of the holy, glorious, and victorious martyrs; of our holy and God-bearing fathers, }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (the patron saint of the temple)}{
\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 ; of the holy and Righteous Ancestors of God Joachim and Anna; of }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (the Saints of the day)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
 and of all the saints: make our prayer acceptable; grant us the remission of our sins; shelter us with the shelter of Thy wings; drive away from us every enemy and adversary; make our life peaceful, O Lord; have mercy 
on us and on Thy world, and save our souls, for Thou art good and the Lover of mankind.
\par }{\cs59\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid7473308 Choir:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs55\i0\insrsid7473308 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain 
\s57\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308\charrsid394076 The Rite of Forgiveness 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid7473308 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Then, making a prostration, the priest saith to the brethren (sisters, congregation):
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  Bless, }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (holy master and) }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 holy fathers }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (mothers)}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
 and brethren, and forgive me a sinner, all wherein I have sinned this day in deed, word, and through all my senses. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 And the brethren (sisters) (congregation) reply: 
\par }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 May God forgive and have mercy on thee, holy father. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 And they make a prostration, asking this forgiveness:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par Bless me, holy father, and forgive all wherein I have sinned this day in deed, word, and thought, and in all my senses, and pray for me a sinner. 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  Through His grace may God forgive and have mercy on us all. 
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7354112 {\f1\fs32\insrsid7354112 ----------
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 And he saith this Ectenia:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest: }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
Let us pray for the Orthodox episcopate of the Russian Church; for our lord the Very Most Reverend Metropolitan N., First Hierarch of the Russian Church Abroad; for our lord the Most Reverend (Archbishop o
r Bishop N., whose diocese it is) and all our brethren in Christ. 
\par }{\cs59\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid7473308 Choir:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Lord, have mercy}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 . (}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 
Quietly, slowly, and repeatedly, until the petitions are finished )
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
 For the suffering Russian land and its Orthodox people both in the homeland and in the diaspora, and for their salvation; for this land, its authorities and armed forces, and for every Christian land. 
\par For them that hate us and them that love us. 
\par For them that are kind to us and them that serve us. 
\par For them that have asked us unworthy ones to pray for them. 
\par For the deliverance of the imprisoned. 
\par For our fathers and brethren that have passed on before us. 
\par For those sailing upon the sea. 
\par For those bedridden in infirmities. 
\par Let us pray for the abundance of the fruits of the earth. 
\par And for every Orthodox Christian soul. 
\par Let us bless pious kings (rulers), Orthodox hierarchs, and the founders of this holy habitation. 
\par Our parents, and all that have passed on before us, our fathers, brethren, and the Orthodox here and everywhere laid to rest. 
\par Let us say also for ourselves. 
\par Choir: Lord, have mercy. }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 Thrice 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\insrsid7473308 Priest:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  For the sake of the intercessions of Thy most pure Mother of }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308 (the patron saint of the temple), }{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308 
and all the saints, O Lord Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us. 
\par }{\cs59\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid7473308 Choir:}{\cs53\b\fs36\insrsid7473308  }{\cs58\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid7473308 Amen.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6953665 {\cs44\i\f1\cf6\insrsid7473308\charrsid6953665 
\par And we venerate the holy icons and receive a blessing from the priest (superior) (bishop).
\par }\pard \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7354112 {\f1\fs32\insrsid7354112 ----------
\par ----------
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7354112 {\insrsid7354112\charrsid7354112 
